WEBVTT

00:04.843 --> 00:06.149
[Claire] Previously...

00:06.280 --> 00:08.151
[Jamie] What do ye think?
Make yerself at home, lad.

00:08.282 --> 00:11.328
No, I dinna ken what I am
or what I believe,

00:11.415 --> 00:13.156
but I'll always have a home
with Uncle Jamie.

00:13.287 --> 00:15.463
[Claire]
I've re-created anesthetic.

00:15.550 --> 00:18.379
It's called ether.
You don't feel a thing.

00:18.509 --> 00:20.207
He doesn't take the slightest
bit of interest

00:20.337 --> 00:22.557
in the subject of healing,
whereas I'm eager to learn.

00:22.687 --> 00:24.820
I dinna ken which side
the Cherokee will fight.

00:24.950 --> 00:27.170
If Chief Bird acquires weapons,
they may be soon pointed at us.

00:27.257 --> 00:28.606
[Young Ian]
It would be a shame

00:28.737 --> 00:30.260
if our Indian neighbors
became our enemies.

00:30.347 --> 00:32.828
[Jamie] Fergus!

00:32.958 --> 00:34.351
Marsali and the children
need ye.

00:34.482 --> 00:36.136
This is for them.

00:36.223 --> 00:38.225
Did you convey my request
for guns to your king?

00:38.355 --> 00:40.096
I've decided against it.

00:40.183 --> 00:41.315
[Young Ian] Brianna told me
of the injustices

00:41.402 --> 00:42.664
the Indians will face.

00:42.794 --> 00:44.927
And if ye wilna help them,
then I will.

00:45.058 --> 00:47.234
[Jamie] He had a child,
with his Mohawk wife.

00:47.364 --> 00:49.149
He fights for them
because they are his family.

00:51.716 --> 00:54.284
[poignant music plays]

00:54.458 --> 00:57.113
♪ ♪

02:02.047 --> 02:06.269
My son, by the ceremony
that was performed this day,

02:06.400 --> 02:08.271
every drop of white blood

02:08.358 --> 02:09.881
has been washed
from your veins.

02:12.057 --> 02:13.755
You are adopted...

02:15.060 --> 02:16.192
...into our great family.

02:18.890 --> 02:20.979
You're flesh of our flesh,

02:21.066 --> 02:23.156
bone of our bone.

02:25.158 --> 02:27.943
You have nothing
to fear from us.

02:28.073 --> 02:30.815
We will love you...

02:30.946 --> 02:33.949
and defend you as we love
and defend one another.

02:37.648 --> 02:39.302
[dog grumbles]

02:39.433 --> 02:41.478
Henceforth, you will be called

02:41.609 --> 02:45.352
Okwaho'rohtsi'ah,

02:45.482 --> 02:46.701
Wolf's Brother.

02:46.831 --> 02:49.878
[all whooping wildly]

02:50.008 --> 02:52.707
[uplifting music plays]

02:52.881 --> 02:55.623
♪ ♪

03:14.816 --> 03:17.253
[man] ♪ Sing me a song ♪

03:17.427 --> 03:20.256
♪ Of a lad that is gone ♪

03:20.430 --> 03:22.824
♪ Say, could that lad ♪

03:22.998 --> 03:25.696
♪ Be I? ♪

03:25.870 --> 03:28.177
♪ Merry of soul ♪

03:28.264 --> 03:30.962
♪ He sailed on a day ♪

03:31.136 --> 03:33.313
♪ Over the sea ♪

03:33.487 --> 03:36.316
♪ To Skye ♪

03:36.490 --> 03:38.883
[woman] ♪ Billow and breeze ♪

03:39.057 --> 03:41.321
♪ Islands and seas ♪

03:41.495 --> 03:47.283
♪ Mountains of rain and sun ♪

03:47.370 --> 03:49.329
-[man] ♪ All that was good ♪
-[woman] ♪ All that was good ♪

03:49.503 --> 03:51.940
[man] ♪ All that was fair ♪

03:52.114 --> 03:53.942
[both] ♪ All that was me ♪

03:54.116 --> 03:57.162
♪ Is gone ♪

03:57.250 --> 03:59.339
♪ Sing me a song ♪

03:59.513 --> 04:02.255
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

04:02.429 --> 04:04.387
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

04:04.735 --> 04:07.477
♪ Be I? ♪

04:07.651 --> 04:09.740
♪ Merry of soul ♪

04:09.914 --> 04:12.656
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

04:12.830 --> 04:16.660
♪ Over the sea ♪

04:16.834 --> 04:22.797
♪ To Skye ♪

04:23.363 --> 04:25.930
[dramatic music plays]

04:26.104 --> 04:28.672
♪ ♪

04:31.240 --> 04:34.025
[man singing in Gaelic]

04:34.112 --> 04:36.898
♪ ♪

04:49.650 --> 04:52.305
[people breathing heavily]

04:54.263 --> 04:57.353
[moaning]

04:59.486 --> 05:01.923
[both sighing contentedly,
chuckling]

05:05.100 --> 05:07.755
"Greased lightning," huh?

05:07.885 --> 05:09.583
What?

05:09.713 --> 05:11.106
Who?

05:11.236 --> 05:14.370
Me, I suppose.

05:14.501 --> 05:16.590
Or were ye not thunderstruck,
there at the end?

05:16.720 --> 05:18.853
[chuckles]

05:18.983 --> 05:21.029
What, did I teach you
that phrase?

05:21.159 --> 05:23.336
Mm, I've heard you use it, aye.

05:23.466 --> 05:25.120
No, that particular figure
of speech

05:25.250 --> 05:28.210
relates to extreme speed,

05:28.341 --> 05:30.734
not lubricated brilliance.

05:30.865 --> 05:32.649
Ah.

05:32.780 --> 05:35.304
-I can be fast, too.
-[chuckles]

05:35.435 --> 05:37.959
Eh, maybe not first thing
in the morning.

05:38.089 --> 05:39.787
There are worse ways
to wake up, though.

05:39.917 --> 05:41.266
Mm.

05:41.397 --> 05:42.485
[person sneezes
in the distance]

05:42.616 --> 05:44.444
[Claire sighs]

05:44.574 --> 05:46.968
[person sneezes
in the distance]

05:47.098 --> 05:49.100
Yes, there are.

05:49.231 --> 05:51.625
[sighs] Poor Major MacDonald.

05:51.755 --> 05:54.192
Imagine being allergic to cats?

05:54.323 --> 05:56.325
Hmm. Can he be allergic
to houseguests?

05:56.456 --> 05:57.674
[both chuckle]

05:57.761 --> 05:59.154
Let's stay in bed, Sassenach.

06:01.156 --> 06:04.333
[distant clattering]

06:04.420 --> 06:06.291
[both sigh]

06:06.422 --> 06:07.423
-Hmm.
-Maybe for a minute.

06:07.510 --> 06:09.643
Mm.

06:09.773 --> 06:13.647
I'm sure Mrs. Bug has spared
no effort on breakfast today.

06:13.777 --> 06:15.039
Mm.

06:15.170 --> 06:16.824
[Major MacDonald sneezes
in the distance]

06:16.954 --> 06:19.783
[sighs]

06:19.914 --> 06:23.091
Did the Major say
how long he intends to stay?

06:23.178 --> 06:25.572
He leaves for New Bern
tomorrow.

06:25.702 --> 06:28.792
I must take the guns
to the Cherokee.

06:28.923 --> 06:31.012
Governor Martin
will be pleased.

06:31.142 --> 06:32.448
Aye.

06:32.579 --> 06:34.624
MacDonald brought a letter

06:34.755 --> 06:39.020
praising my "enterprise in...

06:39.150 --> 06:41.196
"drawing the Cherokee
into the sphere

06:41.326 --> 06:43.633
of British influence
once more."

06:43.764 --> 06:45.635
[Claire]
Mm, we should go down,

06:45.766 --> 06:47.724
or the Major will have eaten
all the honey cakes.

06:47.855 --> 06:51.380
Mmm, honey cakes.

06:51.511 --> 06:52.425
[both chuckle]

06:54.688 --> 06:56.254
[Jamie]
Ye'll leave tomorrow.

06:56.385 --> 06:58.039
Mr. Bug will come with ye.

06:58.169 --> 07:00.389
I'm entrusting you with selling
our trade goods now.

07:00.520 --> 07:02.478
-[Fergus] Thank you, Milord.
-'Tis no small task, lad.

07:02.609 --> 07:04.393
Men like the weight of coin
in their purse.

07:04.524 --> 07:06.395
They'll no wish to part
with it, but, um...

07:06.526 --> 07:08.092
ye're a fine salesman.

07:08.223 --> 07:09.703
I'll try my best.

07:09.833 --> 07:11.356
When ye're finished
in Cross Creek,

07:11.487 --> 07:13.141
pay a visit to Aunt Jocasta.

07:13.228 --> 07:15.535
She'll be pleased
with the company.

07:15.622 --> 07:17.841
Take these broadsheets
to read along yer journey.

07:20.931 --> 07:23.543
I know what you're doing.

07:23.630 --> 07:25.632
What am I doing?

07:25.762 --> 07:27.198
You believe if I can put
some distance

07:27.329 --> 07:29.897
between myself
and my worries...

07:30.027 --> 07:30.724
I will heal.

07:32.726 --> 07:34.597
With time...

07:34.728 --> 07:36.251
aye, I do.

07:44.346 --> 07:47.436
I remember when we used
to print the news ourselves.

07:47.567 --> 07:51.048
Do you ever think
of our time in Edinburgh?

07:51.135 --> 07:52.615
Now and again.

07:52.746 --> 07:55.705
I miss those times.

07:55.792 --> 07:58.360
I had faith in you then, lad.

07:58.491 --> 08:00.971
I have faith in you still.

08:01.058 --> 08:04.105
You must try to find faith in
yourself once again, mon fils.

08:06.020 --> 08:08.501
Thank you, Milord...

08:08.631 --> 08:09.893
for everything.

08:11.765 --> 08:13.767
You've saved
my life more than once.

08:15.986 --> 08:18.902
I've simply balanced
the scales.

08:19.033 --> 08:21.775
[uplifting music plays]

08:21.862 --> 08:24.647
♪ ♪

08:27.998 --> 08:30.305
[birds chirping]

08:30.392 --> 08:31.611
[gunshots]

08:33.308 --> 08:34.918
[objects shattering]

08:37.007 --> 08:38.313
I hit it.

08:40.010 --> 08:41.142
You've been practicing.

08:43.448 --> 08:44.841
I hear the standard
in the army's

08:44.972 --> 08:45.929
two rounds a minute,
is that right, Major?

08:46.060 --> 08:47.888
Indeed.

08:48.018 --> 08:50.368
[Jamie] Of course, there are
some who can manage three.

08:50.455 --> 08:52.632
[Major MacDonald]
Is that so, Mr. Fraser?

08:52.762 --> 08:54.242
Well, it remains to be seen

08:54.372 --> 08:56.157
whether the Cherokee
will ever manage that.

08:56.287 --> 08:59.160
Aye. Maybe they should
stick to their bows.

08:59.247 --> 09:00.770
I can't say these guns
are new,

09:00.901 --> 09:02.903
but they'll kill more
and more quickly

09:03.033 --> 09:04.687
than any arrow.

09:04.818 --> 09:07.516
That's why the Cherokee
want them so badly.

09:07.647 --> 09:11.912
You can tell your Chief
Bird Who Sings in the Evening

09:12.042 --> 09:14.610
that these have been
field-tested and aim true.

09:14.741 --> 09:16.830
I'll tell him they have
yer personal guarantee.

09:16.917 --> 09:18.135
[Young Ian]
Morning.

09:18.266 --> 09:19.746
Sorry?

09:19.833 --> 09:22.357
Chief Twiskwa
Sunale Dekanogisgi--

09:22.487 --> 09:24.664
Chief Bird Who Sings
in the Morning.

09:24.794 --> 09:27.492
Why they won't take
a Christian name is beyond me.

09:27.580 --> 09:31.496
Aye. A simple name
like Donald son of Donald.

09:31.627 --> 09:34.456
[gunshot, object shatters]

09:34.587 --> 09:36.197
[Major MacDonald] In any event,
the governor would like him

09:36.327 --> 09:38.373
to swear an oath,
this Bird of yours,

09:38.503 --> 09:40.854
that he'll fly our way

09:40.984 --> 09:42.551
if the king should call
upon him,

09:42.682 --> 09:45.206
morning or evening.

09:45.293 --> 09:46.990
The king's counting on you,
Mr. Fraser.

09:50.211 --> 09:52.213
[gunshot]

09:52.343 --> 09:54.998
[rain falling]

09:56.739 --> 09:58.175
[Jamie]
Brianna, what's wrong?

10:01.526 --> 10:03.703
It won't be enough...

10:03.790 --> 10:06.270
to save them.

10:06.401 --> 10:08.969
Tell me, a leannan.

10:11.406 --> 10:13.974
About 60 years from now,

10:14.104 --> 10:17.107
the government will force
the Cherokee off their land.

10:17.238 --> 10:20.415
They'll move them
1,000 miles from here.

10:20.545 --> 10:23.374
I ken well what governments
are capable of.

10:23.461 --> 10:25.028
8,000 of them will die.

10:27.727 --> 10:29.337
They'll call it
the Trail of Tears.

10:29.467 --> 10:32.514
[gunshots]

10:32.645 --> 10:33.994
I don't know. I just--

10:34.124 --> 10:36.866
It didn't seem right to know
and not tell you.

10:36.953 --> 10:39.608
[gunshot]

10:39.739 --> 10:42.480
[dramatic music plays]

10:42.655 --> 10:45.440
♪ ♪

11:25.132 --> 11:26.916
[Jamie]
Siyo ginali.

11:27.090 --> 11:29.876
♪ ♪

11:54.727 --> 11:56.119
What is it, lad?

11:58.426 --> 12:00.123
It isn't Cherokee.

12:00.210 --> 12:04.127
A three-feathered gustoweh,
it's Mohawk.

12:05.563 --> 12:08.741
[speaking Mohawk]

12:11.700 --> 12:13.920
Greetings, Wolf's Brother.

12:30.937 --> 12:34.810
When I was first...

12:34.941 --> 12:37.378
learning their language...

12:39.728 --> 12:41.774
...I couldna pronounce
her name properly.

12:44.037 --> 12:45.778
So I called her Emily.

12:47.475 --> 12:49.129
It made her laugh.

12:49.216 --> 12:51.958
♪ ♪

13:04.231 --> 13:08.713
[both speaking Mohawk]

13:10.193 --> 13:14.676
[chuckles, speaking Mohawk]

13:17.244 --> 13:19.333
[speaking Mohawk]

13:19.420 --> 13:22.205
♪ ♪

13:28.342 --> 13:29.604
What is it?

13:32.476 --> 13:34.609
[speaking Mohawk]

13:34.739 --> 13:37.046
Wolf, my clan.

13:37.220 --> 13:40.006
♪ ♪

13:52.888 --> 13:54.107
Hmm.

13:54.281 --> 13:57.023
♪ ♪

14:16.869 --> 14:20.176
I was becoming one of them.

14:20.307 --> 14:22.875
Even Kaheroton
was like my brother.

14:25.486 --> 14:28.054
You're raising
Johiehon's child?

14:28.184 --> 14:30.012
We will all raise her,

14:30.143 --> 14:32.058
but she will stay
with Johiehon's sister.

14:34.277 --> 14:35.888
You loved Johiehon very much,
didn't you?

14:37.498 --> 14:39.065
I did.

14:39.195 --> 14:41.241
But she chose another.

14:41.328 --> 14:43.286
And you?

14:43.417 --> 14:44.679
Will you choose another?

14:46.507 --> 14:49.510
We do not choose,
Okwaho'rohtsi'ah.

14:53.122 --> 14:54.471
They choose.

14:54.558 --> 14:57.300
[peaceful music plays]

14:57.474 --> 15:00.216
♪ ♪

15:19.366 --> 15:22.151
[birds honking]

15:22.325 --> 15:25.111
♪ ♪

15:31.378 --> 15:33.119
[speaking Mohawk]

15:37.210 --> 15:39.952
[repeating in Mohawk]

15:42.693 --> 15:44.652
[speaking Mohawk]

15:44.739 --> 15:46.219
Flower.

15:46.393 --> 15:49.135
♪ ♪

16:05.542 --> 16:07.370
To remind you...

16:09.677 --> 16:11.940
...when we were joined
together

16:12.071 --> 16:13.637
as one.

16:13.811 --> 16:16.640
♪ ♪

16:49.760 --> 16:53.068
[Young Ian moaning]

16:53.199 --> 16:55.984
[speaking Mohawk]

16:58.552 --> 17:01.468
[both moaning]

17:01.555 --> 17:04.297
♪ ♪

17:45.860 --> 17:49.255
[person speaking Mohawk]

18:02.311 --> 18:06.098
[laughter]

18:06.228 --> 18:09.362
You, Wolf's Brother,
you tell us a story.

18:09.492 --> 18:10.667
-No, no, no.
-Yes, you tell us a story.

18:10.798 --> 18:11.799
Yes.

18:14.367 --> 18:16.195
This is my story--

18:16.325 --> 18:19.502
being here
with-with all of you.

18:19.633 --> 18:21.461
I couldn't have a better story.

18:21.591 --> 18:22.679
[people murmur]

18:22.810 --> 18:24.855
W-what
of your-your life before?

18:24.986 --> 18:27.031
I want to hear tales
of your-your great journey

18:27.162 --> 18:29.730
across the sea and the-the
woman with green eyes, the-

18:29.860 --> 18:31.688
the-the Bakra.

18:31.819 --> 18:33.299
-[grunts]
-No.

18:33.429 --> 18:35.388
Let my husband have it.

18:35.518 --> 18:37.216
He tells much better stories
when he's drunk.

18:37.346 --> 18:39.914
[laughter]

18:40.044 --> 18:42.699
So, husband...

18:42.830 --> 18:44.658
tell us about this woman
with green eyes.

18:47.182 --> 18:49.706
Right.

18:49.793 --> 18:53.101
S-she was a--she was a witch...

18:53.232 --> 18:56.104
a-a very wicked woman.

18:56.235 --> 18:59.063
[speaking Mohawk]

19:01.153 --> 19:03.546
I-I'm sorry.
I canna say it in Mohawk.

19:03.677 --> 19:04.634
I dinna have the words.

19:06.941 --> 19:09.422
Sing for us, then...

19:09.552 --> 19:11.337
about your home across the sea.

19:13.382 --> 19:15.689
All right.

19:15.819 --> 19:18.735
[clears throat]
Yeah.

19:18.822 --> 19:20.694
♪ When-- ♪

19:20.868 --> 19:23.349
♪ When the sheep ♪

19:23.523 --> 19:26.830
♪ Are in the fauld ♪

19:27.004 --> 19:31.400
♪ And the kine at hame ♪

19:31.574 --> 19:36.362
♪ And all the weary world ♪

19:36.536 --> 19:41.236
♪ To rest are gane ♪

19:43.151 --> 19:47.547
♪ The waes of my heart ♪

19:47.721 --> 19:52.334
♪ Fall in showers frae my e'e ♪

19:52.508 --> 19:56.208
♪ While my gudeman ♪

19:56.295 --> 19:59.341
♪ Lies sound ♪

19:59.428 --> 20:02.214
♪ By me ♪

20:02.344 --> 20:04.999
[scattered laughter]

20:05.129 --> 20:07.915
[serene music plays]

20:08.089 --> 20:10.831
♪ ♪

20:14.356 --> 20:15.836
Ohraka?

20:15.923 --> 20:18.317
[chuckles]
Ohkara.

20:18.404 --> 20:21.233
♪ ♪

20:21.363 --> 20:23.147
Ohkara.

20:23.278 --> 20:24.018
Mm.

20:26.325 --> 20:28.065
But getting better.

20:28.240 --> 20:31.025
♪ ♪

20:40.426 --> 20:42.254
Ohnehkwentah.

20:42.428 --> 20:45.257
♪ ♪

20:52.960 --> 20:54.788
I dinna always
need words.

20:54.875 --> 20:57.660
♪ ♪

21:09.237 --> 21:11.283
Do you ever miss your home?

21:16.984 --> 21:19.291
You are my home...

21:25.558 --> 21:27.168
...both of you.

21:27.342 --> 21:30.084
♪ ♪

21:38.353 --> 21:40.442
[groans in pain]

21:40.573 --> 21:42.009
Emily?

21:43.924 --> 21:45.795
My love...

21:45.926 --> 21:47.101
is all well?

21:50.322 --> 21:52.106
[groans in pain]

21:54.195 --> 21:55.892
[groans in pain]

21:58.417 --> 22:01.115
-[Young Ian] Oh.
-[groans in pain]

22:01.245 --> 22:03.160
Blessed Michael, defend us.

22:03.291 --> 22:06.120
[shouting in Mohawk]

22:11.299 --> 22:14.215
[gasping]

22:14.302 --> 22:17.044
[sobbing]

22:17.174 --> 22:19.829
[dramatic music plays]

22:20.003 --> 22:22.832
♪ ♪

22:22.963 --> 22:25.922
[crying in pain]

22:26.009 --> 22:28.838
♪ ♪

22:33.800 --> 22:36.150
[cries in pain]

22:38.195 --> 22:39.545
Wahionhaweh!

22:41.155 --> 22:42.765
I must be with her!

22:42.896 --> 22:44.463
It is for the women
to help her now.

22:44.593 --> 22:46.334
Be still.

22:46.465 --> 22:48.858
If you must do something,
go to the woods and pray.

22:50.164 --> 22:51.426
Go.

22:51.600 --> 22:54.386
♪ ♪

23:02.785 --> 23:05.440
[bird hooting in the distance]

23:05.614 --> 23:08.400
♪ ♪

23:10.489 --> 23:14.362
[breathing heavily]

23:14.493 --> 23:17.583
Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

23:17.713 --> 23:19.236
Blessed art thou amongst women,

23:19.367 --> 23:22.414
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

23:22.588 --> 23:25.417
♪ ♪

23:34.208 --> 23:36.428
If the Mohawk Creator
is up there,

23:36.558 --> 23:37.820
please...

23:40.344 --> 23:42.434
...dinna let this be
the hour of death.

23:42.608 --> 23:45.524
♪ ♪

23:45.654 --> 23:47.482
Amen.

23:47.569 --> 23:50.354
♪ ♪

24:00.582 --> 24:02.497
She whose hearth I share?

24:04.325 --> 24:05.935
She lives.

24:07.720 --> 24:09.112
And my child?

24:09.286 --> 24:12.072
♪ ♪

24:23.736 --> 24:25.999
I never saw her...

24:26.129 --> 24:29.219
the bairn.

24:29.306 --> 24:31.091
They'd already wrapped her up.

24:32.745 --> 24:34.224
We buried her in furs.

24:37.967 --> 24:40.100
I'm heartsick for ye, lad.

24:44.234 --> 24:46.498
Emily got with child again.

24:48.282 --> 24:50.110
I was good at that part.

24:53.156 --> 24:55.942
♪ ♪

25:01.425 --> 25:04.603
But it wasna meant to be.

25:04.733 --> 25:07.519
[sobbing]

25:07.693 --> 25:10.173
♪ ♪

25:13.525 --> 25:16.658
[Young Ian] A few months later,
everything changed.

25:16.789 --> 25:19.531
Ian... [speaking Mohawk]

25:22.403 --> 25:25.928
The Creator tells us
that for a woman to conceive,

25:26.059 --> 25:29.149
the man's spirit must do battle
with hers and overcome it.

25:31.499 --> 25:33.545
If his spirit
is not strong enough,

25:33.675 --> 25:37.157
the child cannot take root
in the womb.

25:37.287 --> 25:39.638
There must be something
I can do...

25:39.725 --> 25:41.944
that we can try.

25:42.031 --> 25:45.948
You have been made Mohawk
by an old custom.

25:46.035 --> 25:48.821
But your spirit is not Mohawk.

25:48.951 --> 25:50.474
What?

25:50.605 --> 25:52.172
No.

25:52.302 --> 25:54.435
I ken ye dinna believe that.

25:54.566 --> 25:58.134
'Tis only an excuse because
ye think I'm no' worthy.

25:58.265 --> 26:00.180
Return to your own people.

26:00.310 --> 26:02.312
Among them,
your spirit will be strong.

26:02.443 --> 26:04.793
No.

26:04.924 --> 26:07.491
Wahionhaweh agrees.

26:07.622 --> 26:09.668
No.

26:09.755 --> 26:11.365
She would never.

26:13.541 --> 26:14.934
I must speak with my wife.

26:15.064 --> 26:16.936
You have food for three days.

26:17.066 --> 26:18.981
You are a good hunter.

26:21.375 --> 26:23.029
No.

26:23.116 --> 26:24.596
This is--

26:28.077 --> 26:31.733
I am flesh of her flesh...

26:31.864 --> 26:33.953
bone of her bone.

26:34.127 --> 26:36.825
♪ ♪

27:05.767 --> 27:08.422
[scoffs]

27:08.552 --> 27:09.771
Is this what you want?

27:12.905 --> 27:14.689
-It is what must be.
-Let her speak.

27:14.863 --> 27:17.649
♪ ♪

27:25.091 --> 27:27.310
[voice breaking] Please.

27:27.441 --> 27:29.704
It is what must be.

27:29.878 --> 27:32.402
♪ ♪

27:32.533 --> 27:34.100
Go.

27:34.274 --> 27:37.103
♪ ♪

27:37.233 --> 27:38.452
Leave.

27:40.193 --> 27:41.542
Leave.

27:41.716 --> 27:44.458
♪ ♪

27:56.339 --> 27:59.691
He was my friend, my brother.

28:02.563 --> 28:04.086
He kent how much I loved her.

28:09.613 --> 28:13.400
Was I weak, Uncle Jamie?

28:13.530 --> 28:15.663
Should I have fought harder
for her?

28:17.360 --> 28:19.667
Seems you fought
as hard as you could...

28:22.322 --> 28:24.716
...without taking her by force.

28:27.327 --> 28:30.591
Would you have left...

28:30.722 --> 28:32.680
if it had been Auntie Claire?

28:36.858 --> 28:38.512
It's not the same, lad.

28:42.124 --> 28:45.040
I dinna think I have it in me

28:45.171 --> 28:47.347
to give the rifles
to Chief Bird tonight.

28:49.610 --> 28:52.831
He'll be expecting
a celebration.

28:52.961 --> 28:55.094
Aye.

28:55.181 --> 28:57.661
Dinna fash.

28:57.792 --> 29:00.534
Sleep now.

29:00.664 --> 29:03.232
I'll tell Chief Bird.

29:03.319 --> 29:04.930
We'll do it in the morning.

29:14.156 --> 29:16.942
♪ ♪

29:18.813 --> 29:20.902
[Scotchee]
Well, I never.

29:21.033 --> 29:24.340
You must be Mr. James Fraser
in the flesh.

29:24.471 --> 29:25.907
Alexander Cameron.

29:26.038 --> 29:28.214
-The one they call "Scotchee."
-Aye.

29:28.344 --> 29:30.085
There was a time
I was the only Indian Agent

29:30.216 --> 29:32.044
who could fit that appellation.
[chuckles]

29:32.174 --> 29:34.437
I've heard such tales of ye.

29:34.568 --> 29:37.745
Fair dying was I to meet ye
and see if they were true.

29:37.876 --> 29:39.834
Bear Killer?

29:41.096 --> 29:44.578
I ken the Cherokee have
a deep reverence for bears.

29:44.708 --> 29:45.535
The less said about that,
the better.

29:45.622 --> 29:47.233
[Scotchee chuckles]

29:47.363 --> 29:49.104
You're the, uh, agent
to the Overhill Cherokee,

29:49.191 --> 29:50.802
are ye no'?

29:50.889 --> 29:52.716
-What brings ye east?
-Aye.

29:52.847 --> 29:55.067
We've come to marry off a lass
to Chief Bird and to trade.

29:55.197 --> 29:57.547
I see there is a Mohawk here
trading as well.

29:57.678 --> 29:58.505
Aye.

30:00.724 --> 30:02.335
Bird canna stop himself
from boasting

30:02.465 --> 30:03.771
about the rifles you brought.

30:03.902 --> 30:05.251
A hundred, he said.

30:05.381 --> 30:07.644
Twenty, he'll come to find.

30:07.775 --> 30:09.908
He also said you
might have brought some whisky.

30:10.038 --> 30:11.692
Aye.

30:11.823 --> 30:14.042
Some of my last good barrels.

30:14.173 --> 30:16.131
Care for a wee dram, would you?

30:16.262 --> 30:17.916
[both chuckle]

30:19.918 --> 30:23.051
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

30:24.139 --> 30:25.227
Ooh.

30:27.142 --> 30:29.797
One dram becomes two...

30:29.928 --> 30:31.581
becomes three.

30:33.061 --> 30:35.063
What's after three?

30:35.194 --> 30:39.241
-Twelve in yer case.
-[laughing]

30:39.372 --> 30:41.461
Ahh.

30:41.548 --> 30:43.680
Listen...
[grunts]

30:52.689 --> 30:54.996
...I've acquired land
in Tennessee,

30:55.127 --> 30:57.477
bought
from the Overhill Cherokee.

30:57.564 --> 31:00.306
Others are buying as well.

31:00.436 --> 31:02.438
I can fetch ye a good deal.

31:02.569 --> 31:04.527
Call it a favor
for a fellow Scot.

31:04.658 --> 31:07.487
It's against the treaty
to take land so far west.

31:07.617 --> 31:09.141
The king made a promise
to the Indians

31:09.271 --> 31:10.403
not to settle
beyond the treaty line.

31:10.490 --> 31:12.013
But if the Indians choose
to sell,

31:12.144 --> 31:13.754
then that's
a different matter, eh?

31:13.841 --> 31:15.234
'Tis inevitable,
this push west.

31:15.321 --> 31:17.497
I have enough land.

31:17.627 --> 31:19.978
I dinna be involved
in illegal dealings,

31:20.065 --> 31:21.196
nor should you.

31:21.327 --> 31:22.458
You're risking your neck.

31:22.589 --> 31:25.505
Eh, my neck's
been through worse.

31:25.635 --> 31:27.724
But I was hoping
to interest Chief Bird.

31:27.811 --> 31:30.336
The trouble is...

31:30.466 --> 31:32.207
these damned Mohawk
came along.

31:32.338 --> 31:34.079
If they hear of it,

31:34.209 --> 31:36.298
they'll cause an uproar
and ruin my deal.

31:36.472 --> 31:39.258
♪ ♪

31:47.744 --> 31:50.095
Ye want to put us to sleep...

31:50.225 --> 31:51.661
with that?

31:51.792 --> 31:54.012
Yes, but only
for a few moments.

31:54.142 --> 31:55.839
Is it dangerous?

31:55.970 --> 31:58.146
No. No, not at all.

31:59.582 --> 32:00.844
And Malva?

32:00.975 --> 32:03.369
That's why I need
to do the test.

32:03.499 --> 32:05.501
Now, I can't easily operate
on someone

32:05.632 --> 32:07.329
and give them ether
at the same time,

32:07.460 --> 32:09.288
but Malva's my apprentice.

32:09.418 --> 32:11.899
She needs to practice.

32:12.030 --> 32:14.728
I'll go first, Lizzie,
in case it goes awry.

32:16.817 --> 32:19.037
That's ever so brave
of you, Jo.

32:19.167 --> 32:22.866
Aye, that is brave, Josiah.

32:22.997 --> 32:26.566
Thank ye for yer
concern for me.

32:26.653 --> 32:28.133
Uh, but I'll go first.

32:28.263 --> 32:30.700
I'm no' afraid.

32:30.831 --> 32:32.180
Very well.

32:32.267 --> 32:33.834
Shall we get started?

32:33.921 --> 32:36.793
♪ ♪

32:36.924 --> 32:38.665
Two drops on the cloth.

32:38.839 --> 32:42.103
♪ ♪

32:42.234 --> 32:43.887
Should take effect
pretty quickly.

32:44.018 --> 32:45.324
[Malva]
Aye, Mistress.

32:45.454 --> 32:46.978
[sniffs] Oh, it does smell
queer, doesn't it?

32:47.065 --> 32:49.067
Don't breathe it in.

32:49.197 --> 32:51.678
I don't want you falling over
in the middle of an operation.

32:51.852 --> 32:54.898
♪ ♪

32:55.029 --> 32:56.596
Place it gently on her face.

32:58.728 --> 33:01.166
Now, Lizzie,
I want you to breathe deeply.

33:01.296 --> 33:02.863
Count with me. Ready?

33:02.994 --> 33:05.387
-One...
-One...

33:05.518 --> 33:08.042
-Two...
-Two...

33:10.001 --> 33:10.871
[Claire] Three.

33:11.045 --> 33:13.613
♪ ♪

33:13.743 --> 33:15.049
That was fast.

33:15.223 --> 33:18.009
♪ ♪

33:20.533 --> 33:22.404
Now...

33:22.535 --> 33:24.232
you can feel it
when the patient

33:24.363 --> 33:25.581
starts to come round.

33:25.668 --> 33:27.844
There's a vibration
to the skin.

33:27.975 --> 33:29.150
Place your hand here.

33:32.327 --> 33:34.112
Now, can you feel that?

33:34.242 --> 33:36.679
Aye. I do.

33:36.810 --> 33:38.942
Now, during surgery,

33:39.073 --> 33:41.728
we wouldn't want the patient
to come round so quickly.

33:41.902 --> 33:44.644
♪ ♪

33:46.820 --> 33:48.561
She doesna feel it.

33:48.648 --> 33:50.911
Mistress Fraser says we
could cut someone quite open,

33:51.042 --> 33:53.305
slice into them and get out
what's ailing them,

33:53.435 --> 33:55.611
and they wouldn't feel a thing.

33:55.742 --> 33:57.265
Let's bring
the patient round now.

33:57.352 --> 33:58.745
You can remove the mask.

33:58.919 --> 34:01.661
♪ ♪

34:07.319 --> 34:09.147
[groans softly]

34:09.277 --> 34:11.236
When are ye going to begin?

34:11.366 --> 34:14.456
We did it, Lizzie. It's over.
Ye've been fast asleep.

34:14.587 --> 34:16.937
[scoffs] I havena--

34:18.808 --> 34:20.984
Best way to convince her
is to show her.

34:21.115 --> 34:22.334
Josiah?

34:22.508 --> 34:25.250
♪ ♪

34:26.729 --> 34:30.081
[breathes deeply]

34:36.261 --> 34:39.786
Jesus, Mary, and Joseph.
[exhales sharply]

34:39.916 --> 34:41.831
And he canna wake up
until ye take the mask away?

34:41.962 --> 34:44.007
No.

34:44.138 --> 34:46.271
But you wouldn't want a patient
to be under for too long.

34:49.404 --> 34:51.145
Where does the soul go?

34:51.276 --> 34:53.104
[Claire]
It doesn't go anywhere.

34:53.234 --> 34:54.888
It stays with him.

34:55.018 --> 34:57.978
Well, he's not dead.
He's just asleep.

34:58.109 --> 35:00.502
It's different for everyone.

35:00.633 --> 35:02.330
Sometimes you dream,

35:02.461 --> 35:05.638
especially
right before you wake up.

35:05.725 --> 35:07.509
And, uh,
sometimes you see things,

35:07.640 --> 35:09.163
but it's all in your mind.

35:11.557 --> 35:13.124
You've done wonderfully.
Thank you.

35:19.173 --> 35:22.611
I've never seen the like.

35:22.698 --> 35:26.311
It's as if we killed him and
brought him back to life again.

35:26.441 --> 35:29.792
I see now why my father says
it's devil's work.

35:29.923 --> 35:32.752
He'd say no one but God
has a right to do such things.

35:32.882 --> 35:34.580
Of course he would.

35:36.712 --> 35:38.236
Perhaps you better
not tell him, Mal.

35:38.366 --> 35:39.933
Don't you think it, Mistress.

35:40.063 --> 35:41.543
He'd stop me from coming.

35:45.199 --> 35:47.114
I'm ready.

35:47.245 --> 35:50.291
[laughter]

35:51.553 --> 35:52.424
Oh.

35:54.861 --> 35:57.211
[pleasant music plays]

35:57.385 --> 36:00.127
♪ ♪

36:07.569 --> 36:09.832
King George and
Royal Governor Josiah Martin

36:09.963 --> 36:11.965
send ye these rifles
with their compliments.

36:15.186 --> 36:16.883
They hope ye'll be pleased.

36:17.057 --> 36:19.799
♪ ♪

36:21.757 --> 36:23.324
Whoo!

36:23.455 --> 36:26.762
[all whooping]

36:31.114 --> 36:33.769
My pleasure is not
all they hope for.

36:33.900 --> 36:35.945
No.

36:36.076 --> 36:38.383
A promise of loyalty as well.

36:38.513 --> 36:40.820
I desire that as much
as they do.

36:42.648 --> 36:44.998
Today is a day
of celebration.

36:45.128 --> 36:46.913
Let's have no talk of war.

36:48.697 --> 36:50.395
I'd like you
to greet my new wife.

36:50.569 --> 36:53.267
♪ ♪

36:56.836 --> 37:00.231
She asks for no promise
of loyalty to anyone but her.

37:02.058 --> 37:04.670
[people speaking Cherokee]

37:04.844 --> 37:07.629
♪ ♪

37:09.979 --> 37:12.286
Where is your
faithful brother wolf?

37:12.417 --> 37:15.420
Dinna fear.
He's no' abandoned me.

37:17.509 --> 37:20.207
I've left Rollo at home
with my kin.

37:20.338 --> 37:22.688
There is some who did
not want you to leave.

37:28.955 --> 37:30.435
Did they have a...

37:32.045 --> 37:33.220
A son.

37:33.351 --> 37:36.267
He brings them much joy.

37:36.397 --> 37:38.486
He was walking
when we left home.

37:38.617 --> 37:41.272
[people speaking Cherokee]

37:46.189 --> 37:48.975
[dramatic music plays]

37:49.149 --> 37:52.326
♪ ♪

37:52.457 --> 37:54.981
Ye've turned my wife
against me.

37:55.111 --> 37:56.983
Ye stole her hand.

37:57.113 --> 38:00.943
Let's hear that story
around the fire, shall we?

38:01.074 --> 38:03.294
How you saw one man's happiness
and wanted it for yourself.

38:03.468 --> 38:06.297
♪ ♪

38:11.302 --> 38:12.912
[Scotchee]
What's all this, then?

38:26.055 --> 38:28.319
Ian!
That's enough!

38:30.582 --> 38:32.235
[Scotchee]
Don't need trouble out of you!

38:32.366 --> 38:34.803
Yer trading's done.
Pack and go!

38:34.934 --> 38:37.023
Oh, Bear Killer,

38:37.153 --> 38:39.852
ye ken why these lads
were a-scouting up there?

38:39.982 --> 38:41.897
It's a taunt to their enemies!

38:42.028 --> 38:43.421
Makes it harder to scalp them!

38:43.551 --> 38:44.639
Let him go.

38:44.770 --> 38:46.337
Ye're drunk.

38:50.558 --> 38:51.690
[chuckles]

38:51.864 --> 38:54.519
♪ ♪

38:54.649 --> 38:56.347
[Jamie]
Kaheroton, no!

38:56.477 --> 38:58.784
Put that down.

38:58.871 --> 39:00.916
An apology first.
You insulted me.

39:01.047 --> 39:03.354
Ye want to fight...

39:03.484 --> 39:06.226
we'll do it my way.

39:06.357 --> 39:08.924
Find yerself a pistol.

39:09.055 --> 39:10.839
Meet me back here.

39:10.970 --> 39:13.059
-Ye dinna mean that.
-I accept.

39:13.233 --> 39:15.975
♪ ♪

39:23.025 --> 39:24.984
Ye're better than this.

39:25.114 --> 39:26.681
Surely ye're a friend
to the Indians.

39:26.812 --> 39:29.815
A challenge has been laid
down and accepted.

39:29.989 --> 39:32.774
♪ ♪

40:04.893 --> 40:07.853
God granted him a son

40:07.940 --> 40:09.811
but took my wee girl.

40:13.728 --> 40:15.382
She...

40:15.513 --> 40:17.428
she was no' baptized

40:17.515 --> 40:20.605
or given a name...

40:20.735 --> 40:22.607
Mohawk or Christian.

40:24.260 --> 40:26.349
But to me...

40:26.437 --> 40:28.482
she was Iseabaiìl.

40:35.446 --> 40:37.317
Is it my fault she's gone?

40:37.491 --> 40:40.363
♪ ♪

40:40.451 --> 40:43.802
Is God punishing me?

40:43.932 --> 40:46.848
Bringing him here to remind me?

40:46.979 --> 40:48.459
No, lad.

40:50.461 --> 40:51.810
Dinna think it.

40:51.940 --> 40:53.464
God doesna punish.

40:55.291 --> 40:56.858
We need to trust He has a plan.

40:59.687 --> 41:02.647
He's gracious...

41:02.777 --> 41:04.083
merciful.

41:06.259 --> 41:08.087
If that's true...

41:11.394 --> 41:13.222
...then where is she?

41:17.531 --> 41:19.490
I canna bear the thought.

41:19.620 --> 41:21.796
Poor Iseabaiìl...

41:21.927 --> 41:23.929
wandering...

41:24.016 --> 41:25.539
lost.

41:25.713 --> 41:28.324
♪ ♪

41:32.764 --> 41:34.679
My daughter Faith...

41:36.419 --> 41:37.508
...she was also lost.

41:40.336 --> 41:41.903
And I never held her either.

41:41.990 --> 41:44.732
♪ ♪

41:49.258 --> 41:50.912
I dinna have an answer.

41:53.132 --> 41:55.221
Only..

41:55.308 --> 41:57.484
at the end
of life comes death.

42:00.356 --> 42:02.750
And after death...

42:02.881 --> 42:06.537
we come home to the Lord.

42:06.624 --> 42:08.713
How long
the first shall last...

42:10.715 --> 42:12.717
...we canna say.

42:12.891 --> 42:15.807
♪ ♪

42:15.937 --> 42:17.548
Come.

42:20.159 --> 42:23.162
We shall ask my daughter
to look for yours in Heaven.

42:26.905 --> 42:28.776
I ken she'll find her there.

42:28.950 --> 42:31.866
♪ ♪

42:31.997 --> 42:35.957
[sighs deeply]

42:36.131 --> 42:38.873
♪ ♪

43:03.855 --> 43:05.334
[Young Ian]
'Tis my uncle's weapon.

43:05.465 --> 43:07.206
Finest there is.

43:08.903 --> 43:09.861
Take it.

43:11.297 --> 43:13.516
You would do this for me?

43:13.647 --> 43:15.431
You deserve
a fighting chance.

43:21.046 --> 43:23.788
♪ ♪

43:31.491 --> 43:33.101
If I die...

43:33.232 --> 43:34.625
go to her...

43:37.889 --> 43:39.238
...and to my son...

43:41.936 --> 43:43.503
...and give her this.

43:43.677 --> 43:46.419
♪ ♪

43:48.290 --> 43:50.641
Swear you'll go to her.

43:50.771 --> 43:53.731
Care for her, for them.

43:53.905 --> 43:56.647
♪ ♪

44:01.608 --> 44:02.740
[Chief Bird]
Bear Killer.

44:04.567 --> 44:06.569
I will fight with you,
Bear Killer.

44:06.657 --> 44:07.832
Tell your king.

44:09.877 --> 44:12.488
Twiskwa...

44:12.575 --> 44:14.229
there's something
I wish to tell ye.

44:21.497 --> 44:24.762
The women in my family...

44:24.849 --> 44:28.504
are those who see in dreams
what is to come.

44:30.985 --> 44:32.683
Both my wife and my daughter
have seen something

44:32.770 --> 44:35.294
concerning yer people,

44:35.424 --> 44:36.861
though it grieves me
to tell ye.

44:39.167 --> 44:41.300
Some 60 years from now,

44:41.430 --> 44:43.476
yer people will be taken
from their land...

44:45.696 --> 44:48.263
...from the bones
of their ancestors

44:48.394 --> 44:51.484
and be removed
to a-a new place

44:51.614 --> 44:53.225
far from here.

44:53.355 --> 44:55.053
Many will die on this journey,

44:55.183 --> 44:59.753
so much that the path they
tread will be called, um...

44:59.884 --> 45:02.582
the trail where they wept.

45:03.975 --> 45:06.499
Who will do this?

45:06.629 --> 45:10.851
A man named Winfield Scott,
my daughter says,

45:10.938 --> 45:12.723
a general.

45:15.638 --> 45:18.119
It is good you have given
us the weapons, then.

45:18.250 --> 45:20.469
No.

45:20.600 --> 45:23.559
Twenty muskets against 20,000?

45:23.646 --> 45:25.344
It will no' save ye.

45:25.474 --> 45:27.389
What is the benefit
of your warning, then?

45:29.174 --> 45:30.958
I canna warn many.

45:32.960 --> 45:36.659
Well, if I did,
they would call me a madman.

45:36.790 --> 45:39.053
But I can warn you.

45:39.140 --> 45:42.535
You should not go
to this new place or fight,

45:42.665 --> 45:46.365
but when the time comes,
your people must hide.

45:49.411 --> 45:53.198
Any by hiding, they will, uh,
escape what is to come?

45:53.328 --> 45:54.852
I hope so.

45:54.939 --> 45:57.550
If you pass this warning
to your descendants,

45:57.680 --> 46:00.161
then perhaps
they will escape and live.

46:01.902 --> 46:04.339
I will tell my sons

46:04.470 --> 46:06.733
and my sons' sons,

46:06.864 --> 46:08.648
but we will remember.

46:08.822 --> 46:11.738
♪ ♪

46:11.869 --> 46:14.175
Whoever you fight with...

46:16.177 --> 46:19.006
...be it King George's men...

46:19.137 --> 46:21.182
or our enemies...

46:21.313 --> 46:23.663
fight for yerselves.

46:23.837 --> 46:26.579
♪ ♪

46:35.414 --> 46:37.633
This wife you have...

46:37.720 --> 46:41.159
did you pay a great deal
for her?

46:41.246 --> 46:43.422
She cost me
almost everything I had.

46:45.293 --> 46:46.686
She was worth it.

46:46.860 --> 46:49.602
♪ ♪

47:05.009 --> 47:08.360
Gentlemen,
can ye no' reconcile?

47:08.490 --> 47:12.059
I urge ye both to reconsider.

47:12.190 --> 47:14.279
Over my dead body.

47:14.409 --> 47:15.846
-[gun cocks]
-I will not reconsider.

47:17.673 --> 47:20.328
[Jamie]
Step out the distance, stop,

47:20.415 --> 47:22.722
wait for my command to fire.

47:22.896 --> 47:25.638
♪ ♪

47:26.944 --> 47:29.685
One, two,

47:29.816 --> 47:32.123
three, four, five.

47:32.297 --> 47:34.995
♪ ♪

47:35.126 --> 47:36.997
Ready...

47:37.128 --> 47:38.694
[gunshot]

47:38.781 --> 47:40.218
[people murmuring]

47:40.348 --> 47:41.610
He turned early.

47:41.697 --> 47:44.657
[murmuring continues]

47:46.746 --> 47:50.358
Kaheroton, ye may
return fire at will.

47:54.014 --> 47:57.278
No, no, no,
don't-don't shoot!

47:57.365 --> 47:59.628
I'll leave!
I-I'm a friend to the Indians!

47:59.759 --> 48:01.195
Am I not, Bear Killer?

48:01.326 --> 48:03.110
Tell him!

48:03.241 --> 48:05.243
N-never let it be said that
Scotchee Cameron met his end

48:05.330 --> 48:08.202
over some whisky
a-a-and a comment made in jest!

48:08.333 --> 48:10.770
[breathing rapidly]

48:14.121 --> 48:17.081
He's proven himself a coward.

48:17.211 --> 48:18.996
Let him live with his shame.

48:19.170 --> 48:21.912
♪ ♪

48:27.352 --> 48:29.789
[Young Ian]
Kaheroton.

48:29.876 --> 48:32.661
♪ ♪

48:45.152 --> 48:48.677
God chose you to be with her.

48:48.808 --> 48:51.550
[uplifting music plays]

48:51.724 --> 48:54.466
♪ ♪

50:01.707 --> 50:04.927
I thought I had to choose
who to be...

50:05.015 --> 50:07.408
Wolf's Brother or Ian Murray.

50:09.497 --> 50:11.195
I know now I can be both.

50:13.762 --> 50:15.634
I've been known
by many names, lad.

50:18.332 --> 50:19.812
Call yerself whatever ye want.

50:23.598 --> 50:26.775
All that matters
is who ye are here.

50:26.862 --> 50:29.648
♪ ♪

50:34.740 --> 50:36.524
[Young Ian grunts]

50:36.698 --> 50:39.484
♪ ♪

50:58.459 --> 51:01.680
[Keziah]
What was it like?

51:01.810 --> 51:05.945
They put some drops in a mask
and had me breathe it in...

51:06.076 --> 51:09.296
and all went dark.

51:09.427 --> 51:12.082
-[chuckles]
-That quick, Kezzie.

51:17.087 --> 51:18.349
Was it fearsome?

51:18.479 --> 51:21.134
[scoffs] No.

51:23.702 --> 51:26.444
Ye're not afraid
of much, though...

51:26.531 --> 51:27.793
are ye, Lizzie?

51:50.381 --> 51:52.731
What is it you write
in your book?

51:52.861 --> 51:55.429
Mainly recipes for medicines

51:55.560 --> 51:58.606
but also surgical notes.

51:58.737 --> 52:01.131
[pencil scratching]

52:01.261 --> 52:03.307
Would you like to take a look?

52:17.538 --> 52:19.671
Why do you write down
the things that you've done?

52:19.801 --> 52:21.542
The recipes I can see
how you could forget,

52:21.673 --> 52:24.110
but...

52:24.241 --> 52:26.678
why do you do
these drawings and...

52:26.808 --> 52:28.419
write down how you took off
a toe with frost-rot

52:28.549 --> 52:30.290
-and the like?
-[chuckles]

52:30.377 --> 52:33.337
Because every person's body
is different.

52:33.467 --> 52:36.601
But, well,
the most important reason

52:36.731 --> 52:39.343
is so that others can benefit
from what I've learned.

52:39.473 --> 52:41.171
-Like me?
-Yes.

52:43.564 --> 52:45.175
You're doing very well,
by the way.

52:47.307 --> 52:48.787
Mm.

52:48.917 --> 52:51.137
-My brother doesn't like it...
-[sighs]

52:51.268 --> 52:53.226
...but then I'll tell him

52:53.357 --> 52:55.489
I've had a look
in your wee book

52:55.620 --> 52:57.752
and there's nothing
by way of spells in it.

52:57.883 --> 52:59.406
Spells?

52:59.493 --> 53:01.147
Is that what he thinks?

53:01.234 --> 53:03.454
He warned me not to touch it...

53:03.584 --> 53:05.456
for fear of ensorcellment.

53:08.589 --> 53:10.374
But I do find it enchanting.

53:14.204 --> 53:15.944
Well, I'm glad.

53:16.031 --> 53:17.642
[horse neighs in the distance]

53:17.772 --> 53:20.906
[wagon rattling]

53:29.131 --> 53:32.613
Malva, would you mind staying
to straighten up?

53:38.140 --> 53:40.317
[door opens, closes]

53:48.238 --> 53:51.632
You're back a day later
than I expected.

53:51.763 --> 53:53.330
-Was there trouble?
-Hmm.

53:56.985 --> 53:58.987
Aye, only a slight delay.

53:59.118 --> 53:59.858
Hmm.

54:01.468 --> 54:04.210
There were Mohawk there...

54:04.341 --> 54:05.646
men Ian kent.

54:09.389 --> 54:11.391
Oh...

54:11.522 --> 54:13.741
He told me everything
that happened to him.

54:13.872 --> 54:15.787
But, uh...

54:15.917 --> 54:19.617
dinna think I have the strength
to tell it now.

54:19.747 --> 54:21.575
Maybe tomorrow.

54:21.706 --> 54:23.621
Of course.

54:29.757 --> 54:32.543
He said he'd always be
a Mohawk...

54:32.673 --> 54:35.328
and he'll always be Scottish.

54:35.459 --> 54:37.069
He's found a way to be both.

54:39.724 --> 54:42.248
That's a good thing, isn't it?

54:44.337 --> 54:45.295
Aye.

54:49.734 --> 54:51.170
[sighs]

54:51.301 --> 54:54.478
But I canna be two things
at once, Claire...

54:54.608 --> 54:56.480
a rebel, a loyalist...

54:58.525 --> 55:01.963
...agent for the Crown
and an enemy of the king.

55:02.094 --> 55:03.704
It's pulling me apart.

55:07.055 --> 55:09.667
It's time to change horses.

55:09.797 --> 55:13.584
I will resign as Indian Agent.

55:13.714 --> 55:16.717
I'll write the letter tomorrow.

55:16.848 --> 55:21.069
You know, last time...

55:21.200 --> 55:24.116
you came back
from the Cherokee...

55:24.203 --> 55:25.987
[exhales deeply]

55:26.118 --> 55:28.163
...you could hardly
keep your hands off me.

55:28.294 --> 55:30.992
[light music plays]

55:31.166 --> 55:32.733
♪ ♪

55:32.864 --> 55:35.345
I feel a wee bit
more tired this time.

55:35.519 --> 55:38.348
♪ ♪

55:38.478 --> 55:40.175
Well, I hope not too tired.

55:40.350 --> 55:43.135
♪ ♪

55:52.884 --> 55:55.626
[dramatic music plays]

55:55.800 --> 55:58.542
♪ ♪

57:19.013 --> 57:20.188
[wind blows, seagull cries]
